%N A388287 Numbers whose sum of digits in any base b >= 2 is not divisible by b.
%C A388287 All the terms above 1 are even because the sum of digits of 2*m+1 in base m+1, for m >= 1, equals m+1. In general, the sum of digits of k*m+1 in base m+1, for k >= 2 and m >= k-1, equals m+1, and thus k*m+1 is not a term. Therefore, all the terms above 2 are of the form p + 1, where p is an odd prime.
%H A388287 Amiram Eldar, <a href="/A388287/b388287.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%p A388287 filter:= proc(n) local b;
%p A388287   for b from 2 while b^2 < n do
%p A388287     if convert(convert(n,base,b),`+`) mod b = 0 then return false fi
%p A388287   od;
%p A388287   true
%p A388287 end proc:
%p A388287 select(filter, [1, 2, seq(ithprime(i)+1, i=1..1000)]); # _Robert Israel_, Sep 18 2025
%t A388287 q[k_] := k == 1 || k == 2 || (k > 3 && PrimeQ[k-1] && AllTrue[Range[2, Sqrt[k]], !Divisible[DigitSum[k, #], #] &]); Select[Range[6000], q]
%o A388287 (PARI) isok(k) = if(k == 1 || k == 2, 1, if(k > 3 && isprime(k-1), for(b = 2, sqrtint(k), if(!(sumdigits(k, b) % b), return(0))); 1));
